div.p: Dear Maquoketa CSD Students and Families,

Thank You for your patience, flexibility and understanding during these unprecedented times. Our goal is to provide consistent, continuous and clear communication about how we are supporting our staff, students and families. In order to support students and their continued learning, the district is providing a variety of services and support opportunities. We are still uncertain whether or not the Department of Education will be asking districts to make up these hours/days with students; however, we are all in agreement that we want to continue to offer learning opportunities for students. Please use this website to access grade level web links that have been recommended by your child's teachers. In addition, there are PDF links to the learning packets that have been developed. If you would like these mailed to you please complete this google form.

p.style: margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; padding-left: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;

div.p: Finally, please take care of your children and families during this time. This will not be an easy time for many but TOGETHER we will make it through and persevere in the end. Our students, their families, and our staff are our most important priority. Stay safe and please contact your building administrator, or myself if you have questions.
